---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Berkeley Plumbing — C-36 Licensed Plumber | Newbury Park, CA"
  description="Berkeley Plumbing is a solo C-36 licensed plumbing contractor based in Newbury Park, CA. PHCC-trained journeyman specializing in custom homes, new construction, and ADUs. CSLB #1115151."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 text-white py-16 lg:py-24 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-copper font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">About</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-5">
        Berkeley Plumbing
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-300 text-lg leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        C-36 licensed plumbing contractor based in Newbury Park, CA. Specializing in new construction, custom remodels, and ADUs for the Conejo Valley's most demanding residential projects.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main about content -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-12">

      <div class="lg:col-span-2 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900">One Plumber. Full Accountability.</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Berkeley Plumbing is a solo plumbing contracting business. There's no crew of rotating technicians, no dispatcher in the middle, and no subcontracting the actual work. When you hire Berkeley Plumbing, the C-36 licensed journeyman who shows up is the same person you spoke with, who priced the job, and who handles every step through final inspection.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          That model of accountability matters on complex projects. Remodels, ADU builds, and new construction require continuity. When something needs to be revisited, whether it's a change in plans, a coordination issue with another trade, or a question from the inspector, there's one person who knows the full picture of the job.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-8">Background and Training</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Berkeley Plumbing holds a C-36 Plumbing Contractor license from the California State License Board (CSLB #1115151). The C-36 is the license classification required to perform full plumbing work on any residential or commercial construction project in California. It's not a handyman registration or a general contractor add-on: it's a plumbing-specific contractor credential.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Trade education was completed through PHCC (Plumbing Heating Cooling Contractors), one of the longest-standing trade organizations in the industry. PHCC training covers system design, code interpretation, and the technical standards that separate journeyman-level work from basic service calls.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-8">Specialization</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Most of Berkeley Plumbing's work falls into three categories: new construction plumbing on custom homes and multi-unit builds, remodel plumbing for kitchen and bath renovations and whole-home repipes, and ADU plumbing from rough-in through final inspection.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          This focus on construction and remodel work means the projects are more complex than a standard service call, and the customers tend to be more sophisticated: homeowners who have done renovations before, general contractors looking for a reliable sub, and design teams who need a plumber who reads plans and communicates clearly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          All work is performed to California Plumbing Code and designed to pass inspection on the first visit. Upfront pricing means the scope and cost are agreed before any work begins.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-navy-900 mt-8">Service Area</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          Based at 839 Jenny Dr in Newbury Park, Berkeley Plumbing serves the Conejo Valley including Agoura Hills, Thousand Oaks, Westlake Village, Calabasas, Oak Park, and Moorpark. Projects in adjacent communities are considered on a case-by-case basis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar credentials -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-1">
        <div class="bg-stone-warm rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100 sticky top-24">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy-900 mb-5">Credentials</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm">
            <li class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-navy-900">CSLB License #1115151</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-0.5">California State Contractors License Board</p>
              <a
                href="https://www.cslb.ca.gov/onlineservices/checklicenseII/LicenseDetail.aspx?LicNum=1115151"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-copper text-xs hover:underline mt-1 inline-block"
              >
                Verify on CSLB.ca.gov →
              </a>
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-navy-900">C-36 Plumbing Contractor</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The California license for full plumbing contracting on any residential or commercial project</p>
            </li>
            <li class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-navy-900">PHCC-Trained Journeyman</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Plumbing Heating Cooling Contractors trade education</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="font-semibold text-navy-900">Licensed and Insured</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Full liability coverage on every project</p>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-slate-200">
            <a
              href="/contact/"
              class="block w-full bg-copper hover:bg-copper-light text-white font-semibold py-3 px-5 rounded text-center transition-colors mb-3"
            >
              Request an Estimate
            </a>
            <a
              href="tel:(310) 733-7808"
              class="block w-full border border-slate-300 text-slate-700 font-semibold py-3 px-5 rounded text-center transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Call (310) 733-7808
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
